 exquisitely detailed watercolours, this is an inspirational guide to exploring our age-old relationship with plants. Readers will discover the hidden secrets of the plants that surround us and, through this, will be able to reconnect with our place in nature. We have relied on plants throughout our history. We still do, and, with luck, we always will.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aBotany, MedicalxHistory. 0aHerbalsxHistory. 0aHerbsxTherapeutic use. 7aGARDENING / Flowers / Wildflowers.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2024z978311074979340uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/9780300277340?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300277340423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300277340/original  a978-3-11-074979-3  Yale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2024b2024  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles